People flock together when they face the external enemy, while they split up when they face internal enemy.

http://comic.naver.com/webtoon/detail.nhn?titleId=631780&no=24&weekday=tue








Homophilous vs heterophilous

people tend to get away from the group if the group is too clustered (high modularity), while they try to be in a group when there's no group at all (low modularity).
